article.headline: Colorado St. 78, Utah 65
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Andy Ogide finished with 24 points and 10 rebounds as Colorado State ended a season-high three-game losing streak with a 78-65 victory over Utah on Wednesday night It was the 17th career double-double for Ogide, who played his final home game for the Rams (19-10, 9-6 Mountain West). Jesse Carr added 13 points. Josh Watkins scored 22 points and Jason Washburn had 12 for the Utes (13-16, 6-9), who had their three-game winning snapped. Colorado State reached 19 wins for the first time since the 2002-03 season and won nine games in the Mountain West for the first time since joining the conference for the 1999-2000 season. Colorado State was 24 for 26 from the free throw line in completing the regular season sweep of Utah for the second straight year.
